news.title: Land acquired after possession & payment of compensation vests with state: SC
news.para: A vacation bench of justices M R Shah and Aniruddha Bose agreed with the view of the Allahabad High Court that any person retaining possession of the land thereafter has to be treated as a trespasser.

news.title: About 500 houses 'dilapidated', tough time ahead for Bhopal civic body
news.para: Last count by the Bhopal Municipal Corporation (BMC) identified around 500 buildings as dilapidated. Demolition is not an outright option, given most of these structures are under litigation, according to BMC.

news.title: Noida authority's plan to shift slum dwellers hits hurdle
news.para: Launched in 2011, the Jhuggi Jhopri Rehabilitation Scheme was introduced by the Noida Authority to shift slum dwellers into flats in the city.

news.title: About 35% of buildings surveyed in Gujarat are illegal
news.para: The reasons include the addition of floors, the change of use of buildings, and jurisdictional issues. If penalty measures were to be executed for buildings without the BU nod, then it would lead to extensive demolitions.

news.title: Gurugram civic body plans to construct infra facilities, housing projects on urban vacant land
news.para: The major projects planned by the MCG include hospitals, group housing societies, commercial complexes, women’s college, electric vehicle stations, shop-cum-office spaces and sports facilities.

news.title: About 20 lakh houses sanctioned to Andhra Pradesh: Housing minister
news.para: Hardeep Singh Puri said 20 lakh houses have been sanctioned to Andhra Pradesh under various verticals of ‘housing for all’

news.title: Adani group to raise as much as $4.5 billion via a mix of offshore loans
news.para: Proceeds from the latest round of fundraising will be used to part-finance the acquisition of Holcim’s stakes in the two Mumbai-listed cement companies – Ambuja Cements and ACC.

news.title: Residents of Ajnara Le Garden hit streets in Noida over unfinished facilities
news.para: ​The residents, who have been protesting for the past 71 days, were joined by their neighbours at Ajnara Homes in Sector 16B, where the builder is yet to finish the construction of two towers.

news.title: About 4.8 lakh homes worth Rs 4.48 lakh crore stuck or delayed in top seven cities
news.para: For its research, Anarock has taken only those housing projects that were launched in 2014 or before across seven cities -- Delhi-NCR, Mumbai Metropolitan Region (MMR), Kolkata, Chennai, Bengaluru, Hyderabad and Pune.

news.title: Property mutation goes fully online, no manual process allowed now in Delhi
news.para: According to MCD, the certificate can be downloaded by the public on MCD’s website, which will be a QR code enabled computer-generated certificate requiring no signature.

news.title: No fee or Kolkata civic body permission needed for paint, repair job: Mayor
news.para: Hakim on Saturday told TOI that if anyone encountered harassment or were asked to pay money to carry out repairs of their houses, either internal or external, they could contact him.

news.title: Kolkata: Extra 'floor area ratio' hope for Bowbazar buildings
news.para: ​Mayor Firhad Hakim on Saturday said efforts were on to offer extra floor area ratio (FAR) at the time of reconstruction to those residents of Durga Pithuri Lane whose houses would need to be demolished.

news.title: Kanpur development body carries out demolition drive against illegal construction
news.para: The KDA demolished the illegal construction being carried out in premises no.01-Part 112/08-A Benjhabar owned by Ishtiaq Ahmad who had got sanctioned the building plan for residential purposes but raised the building for commercial purposes.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP to check residences converted into commercial set-ups
news.para: ​In Bengaluru, it is common for many residences to be converted as hotels, shops or any commercial establishments. Now, this civic agency has decided to set up squads to check these places so that property tax can be extracted.

news.title: Rights of construction workers are only on paper: Experts
news.para: Experts say the safety of workers at construction sites is often ignored because contractors find it is easier to pay some negotiated amount to the families of the deceased in such cases than to incur a recurring cost of overhauling and modernising their facilities.
